-9e05-a950f1647e51\",\"version\":\"2.1.53\",\"gitBranch\":\"remove-auto-commit\",\"slug\":\"crispy-gathering-origami\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Vz7xcx7QbT5YmjiNqDsamB\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Sessions and Checkpoints\\n     2→\\n     3→## Overview\\n     4→\\n     5→Entire CLI creates checkpoints for AI coding sessions. The system is agent-agnostic - it works with Claude Code, Gemini CLI, OpenCode, or any tool that triggers Entire hooks.\\n     6→\\n     7→## Domain Model\\n     8→\\n     9→### Session\\n    10→\\n    11→A **Session** is a unit of work. Defined in `strategy/session.go`:\\n    12→\\n    13→```go\\n    14→type Session struct {\\n    15→    ID          string       // e.g., \\\"2025-12-01-8f76b0e8-b8f1-4a87-9186-848bdd83d62e\\\"\\n    16→    Description string       // Human-readable summary (first prompt or derived)\\n    17→    Strategy    string       // Strategy that created this session\\n    18→    StartTime   time.Time\\n    19→    Checkpoints []Checkpoint\\n    20→}\\n    21→```\\n    22→\\n    23→### Checkpoint\\n    24→\\n    25→A **Checkpoint** captures a point-in-time within a session. Defined in `strategy/session.go`:\\n    26→\\n    27→```go\\n    28→type Checkpoint struct {\\n    29→    CheckpointID     id.CheckpointID // Stable 12-hex-char identifier\\n    30→    Message          string          // Commit message or checkpoint description\\n    31→    Timestamp        time.Time\\n    32→    IsTaskCheckpoint bool            // Task checkpoint (subagent) vs session checkpoint\\n    33→    ToolUseID        string          // Tool use ID for task checkpoints (empty for session)\\n    34→}\\n    35→```\\n    36→\\n    37→### Checkpoint Types\\n    38→\\n    39→The low-level `checkpoint.Type` (from `checkpoint/checkpoint.go`) indicates storage location:\\n    40→\\n    41→```go\\n    42→type Type int\\n    43→\\n    44→const (\\n    45→    Temporary Type = iota // Full state snapshot, shadow branch\\n    46→    Committed             // Metadata + commit ref, entire/checkpoints/v1\\n    47→)\\n    48→```\\n    49→\\n    50→| Type | Contents | Use Case |\\n    51→|------|----------|----------|\\n    52→| Temporary | Full state (code + metadata) | Intra-session rewind, pre-commit |\\n    53→| Committed | Metadata + commit reference | Permanent record, post-commit rewind |\\n    54→\\n    55→## Interface\\n    56→\\n    57→### Session Operations\\n    58→\\n    59→Sessions are accessed via standalone functions in `strategy/session.go`:\\n    60→\\n    61→```go\\n    62→// ListSessions returns all sessions from entire/checkpoints/v1,\\n    63→// plus additional sessions from strategies implementing SessionSource.\\n    64→func ListSessions() ([]Session, error)\\n    65→\\n    66→// GetSession finds a session by ID (supports prefix matching).\\n    67→func GetSession(sessionID string) (*Session, error)\\n    68→```\\n    69→\\n    70→### Checkpoint Storage (Low-Level)\\n    71→\\n    72→The `checkpoint.Store` interface (from `checkpoint/checkpoint.go`) provides primitives for reading/writing checkpoints. Used by strategies.\\n    73→\\n    74→```go\\n    75→type Store interface {\\n    76→    // Temporary checkpoint operations (shadow branches - full state)\\n    77→    WriteTemporary(ctx context.Context, opts WriteTemporaryOptions) (WriteTemporaryResult, error)\\n    78→    ReadTemporary(ctx context.Context, baseCommit, worktreeID string) (*ReadTemporaryResult, error)\\n    79→    ListTemporary(ctx context.Context) ([]TemporaryInfo, error)\\n    80→\\n    81→    // Committed checkpoint operations (entire/checkpoints/v1 branch - metadata only)\\n    82→    WriteCommitted(ctx context.Context, opts WriteCommittedOptions) error\\n    83→    ReadCommitted(ctx context.Context, checkpointID id.CheckpointID) (*CheckpointSummary, error)\\n    84→    ReadSessionContent(ctx context.Context, checkpointID id.CheckpointID, sessionIndex int) (*SessionContent, error)\\n    85→    ReadSessionContentByID(ctx context.Context, checkpointID id.CheckpointID, sessionID string) (*SessionContent, error)\\n    86→    ListCommitted(ctx context.Context) ([]CommittedInfo, error)\\n    87→}\\n    88→```\\n    89→\\n    90→Key option types (abbreviated):\\n    91→\\n    92→```go\\n    93→type WriteTemporaryOptions struct {\\n    94→    SessionID      string\\n    95→    BaseCommit     string\\n    96→    WorktreeID     string   // Internal git worktree identifier (empty for main)\\n    97→    ModifiedFiles  []string\\n    98→    NewFiles       []string\\n    99→    DeletedFiles   []string\\n   100→    MetadataDir    string   // Relative path to metadata directory\\n   101→    MetadataDirAbs string   // Absolute path\\n   102→    CommitMessage  string\\n   103→    // ...\\n   104→}\\n   105→\\n   106→type WriteCommittedOptions struct {\\n   107→    CheckpointID id.CheckpointID\\n   108→    SessionID    string\\n   109→    Strategy     string\\n   110→    Branch       string\\n   111→    Transcript   []byte\\n   112→    Prompts      []string\\n   113→    Context      []byte\\n   114→    FilesTouched []string\\n   115→    TokenUsage   *agent.TokenUsage\\n   116→    // ...\\n   117→}\\n   118→```\\n   119→\\n   120→Token usage is defined in `agent/types.go`:\\n   121→\\n   122→```go\\n   123→type TokenUsage struct {\\n   124→    InputTokens         int         `json:\\\"input_tokens\\\"`\\n   125→    CacheCreationTokens int         `json:\\\"cache_creation_tokens\\\"`\\n   126→    CacheReadTokens     int         `json:\\\"cache_read_tokens\\\"`\\n   127→    OutputTokens        int         `json:\\\"output_tokens\\\"`\\n   128→    APICallCount        int         `json:\\\"api_call_count\\\"`\\n   129→    SubagentTokens      *TokenUsage `json:\\\"subagent_tokens,omitempty\\\"`\\n   130→}\\n   131→```\\n   132→\\n   133→### Strategy-Level Operations\\n   134→\\n   135→Strategies compose low-level primitives into higher-level workflows.\\n   136→\\n   137→**Manual-commit** has condensation logic:\\n   138→\\n   139→```go\\n   140→// CondenseSession reads accumulated temporary state and writes a committed checkpoint.\\n   141→func (s *ManualCommitStrategy) CondenseSession(\\n   142→    repo *git.Repository,\\n   143→    checkpointID id.CheckpointID,\\n   144→    state *SessionState,\\n   145→) (*CondenseResult, error)\\n   146→```\\n   147→\\n   148→## Storage\\n   149→\\n   150→| Type | Location | Contents |\\n   151→|------|----------|----------|\\n   152→| Session State | `.git/entire-sessions/<id>.json` | Active session tracking |\\n   153→| Temporary | `entire/<commit[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>` branch | Full state (code + metadata) |\\n   154→| Committed | `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch (sharded) | Metadata + commit reference |\\n   155→\\n   156→### Session State\\n   157→\\n   158→Location: `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json`\\n   159→\\n   160→Stored in git common dir (shared across worktrees). Tracks active session info.\\n   161→\\n   162→### Temporary Checkpoints\\n   163→\\n   164→Branch: `entire/<commit[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>`\\n   165→\\n   166→Contains full worktree snapshot plus metadata overlay. **Multiple concurrent sessions** can share the same shadow branch - their checkpoints interleave:\\n   167→\\n   168→```\\n   169→<worktree files...>\\n   170→.entire/metadata/<session-id-1>/\\n   171→├── full.jsonl           # Session 1 transcript\\n   172→├── prompt.txt           # User prompts\\n   173→├── context.md           # Generated context\\n   174→└── tasks/<tool-use-id>/ # Task checkpoints\\n   175→.entire/metadata/<session-id-2>/\\n   176→├── full.jsonl           # Session 2 transcript (concurrent)\\n   177→├── ...\\n   178→```\\n   179→\\n   180→Tied to a base commit. Condensed to committed on user commit.\\n   181→\\n   182→**Shadow branch lifecycle:**\\n   183→- Created on first checkpoint for a base commit\\n   184→- Migrated automatically if base commit changes (stash → pull → apply scenario)\\n   185→- Deleted after condensation to `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n   186→- Reset if orphaned (no session state file exists)\\n   187→\\n   188→### Committed Checkpoints\\n   189→\\n   190→Branch: `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n   191→\\n   192→Metadata only, sharded by checkpoint ID. Supports **multiple sessions per checkpoint**:\\n   193→\\n   194→```\\n   195→<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/\\n   196→├── metadata.json        # CheckpointSummary (aggregated stats)\\n   197→├── 0/                   # First session (0-based indexing)\\n   198→│   ├── metadata.json    # Session-specific CommittedMetadata\\n   199→│   ├── full.jsonl\\n   200→│   ├── prompt.txt\\n   201→│   ├── context.md\\n   202→│   └── content_hash.txt\\n   203→├── 1/                   # Second session\\n   204→│   ├── metadata.json\\n   205→│   ├── full.jsonl\\n   206→│   └── ...\\n   207→└── 2/                   # Third session...\\n   208→```\\n   209→\\n   210→**Root-level metadata.json (`CheckpointSummary`):**\\n   211→```json\\n   212→{\\n   213→  \\\"checkpoint_id\\\": \\\"abc123def456\\\",\\n   214→  \\\"strategy\\\": \\\"manual-commit\\\",\\n   215→  \\\"branch\\\": \\\"main\\\",\\n   216→  \\\"checkpoints_count\\\": 3,\\n   217→  \\\"files_touched\\\": [\\\"file1.txt\\\", \\\"file2.txt\\\"],\\n   218→  \\\"sessions\\\": [\\n   219→    {\\n   220→      \\\"metadata\\\": \\\"/ab/c123def456/0/metadata.json\\\",\\n   221→      \\\"transcript\\\": \\\"/ab/c123def456/0/full.jsonl\\\",\\n   222→      \\\"context\\\": \\\"/ab/c123def456/0/context.md\\\",\\n   223→      \\\"content_hash\\\": \\\"/ab/c123def456/0/content_hash.txt\\\",\\n   224→      \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"/ab/c123def456/0/prompt.txt\\\"\\n   225→    }\\n   226→  ],\\n   227→  \\\"token_usage\\\": {\\n   228→    \\\"input_tokens\\\": 1500,\\n   229→    \\\"cache_creation_tokens\\\": 200,\\n   230→    \\\"cache_read_tokens\\\": 800,\\n   231→    \\\"output_tokens\\\": 500,\\n   232→    \\\"api_call_count\\\": 3\\n   233→  }\\n   234→}\\n   235→```\\n   236→\\n   237→When condensing multiple concurrent sessions:\\n   238→- All sessions are stored in numbered subdirectories using 0-based indexing (`0/`, `1/`, `2/`, ...)\\n   239→- Each `session_id` is assigned a stable index; subsequent writes for the same session reuse the same numbered folder\\n   240→- New `session_id` values are appended at the next index, so higher-numbered folders correspond to more recently introduced sessions, not necessarily the chronologically latest activity\\n   241→- `sessions` array in `CheckpointSummary` maps each session to its file paths\\n   242→- `files_touched` is merged from all sessions\\n   243→\\n   244→### Checkpoint ID Linking\\n   245→\\n   246→The checkpoint ID is the **stable identifier** that links user commits to metadata across branches.\\n   247→\\n   248→**Format:** 12-hex-character random ID (e.g., `a3b2c4d5e6f7`)\\n   249→\\n   250→**Generation:**\\n   251→- Manual-commit: Generated during condensation (post-commit hook)\\n   252→- Auto-commit: Generated when creating the commit\\n   253→\\n   254→**Usage:**\\n   255→\\n   256→1. **User commit trailer** (both strategies):\\n   257→   - `Entire-Checkpoint: a3b2c4d5e6f7` added to user's commit message\\n   258→   - Auto-commit: Added programmatically\\n   259→   - Manual-commit: Added by `prepare-commit-msg` hook (user can remove)\\n   260→\\n   261→2. **Directory sharding** on `entire/checkpoints/v1`:\\n   262→   - Path: `<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/` (e.g., `a3/b2c4d5e6f7/`)\\n   263→   - First 2 chars = shard (256 possible shards)\\n   264→   - Remaining 10 chars = directory name\\n   265→\\n   266→3. **Commit subject** on `entire/checkpoints/v1`:\\n   267→   - Format: `Checkpoint: a3b2c4d5e6f7`\\n   268→   - Makes `git log entire/checkpoints/v1` readable\\n   269→\\n   270→**Bidirectional Lookup:**\\n   271→\\n   272→```\\n   273→User commit → Metadata:\\n   274→  1. Extract \\\"Entire-Checkpoint: a3b2c4d5e6f7\\\" from commit message\\n   275→  2. Read entire/checkpoints/v1 tree at a3/b2c4d5e6f7/\\n   276→\\n   277→Metadata → User commits:\\n   278→  Given checkpoint ID a3b2c4d5e6f7\\n   279→  → Search branch history for commits with \\\"Entire-Checkpoint: a3b2c4d5e6f7\\\"\\n   280→```\\n   281→\\n   282→Note: Commit subjects on `entire/checkpoints/v1` (e.g., `Checkpoint: a3b2c4d5e6f7`)\\n   283→are for human readability in `git log` only. The CLI always reads from the tree at HEAD.\\n   284→\\n   285→**Example Flow:**\\n   286→\\n   287→```\\n   288→                    User creates commit\\n   289→                           ↓\\n   290→           prepare-commit-msg hook adds trailer\\n   291→                           ↓\\n   292→┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\\n   293→│ Commit on main branch:                           │\\n   294→│   \\\"Implement login feature                       │\\n   295→│                                                   │\\n   296→│   Entire-Checkpoint: a3b2c4d5e6f7\\\"               │\\n   297→└──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\\n   298→                           ↓\\n   299→                  post-commit hook runs\\n   300→                           ↓\\n   301→          Condense shadow → entire/checkpoints/v1\\n   302→                           ↓\\n   303→┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\\n   304→│ Commit on entire/checkpoints/v1:                 │\\n   305→│   Subject: \\\"Checkpoint: a3b2c4d5e6f7\\\"            │\\n   306→│                                                   │\\n   307→│   Tree: a3/b2c4d5e6f7/                           │\\n   308→│     ├── metadata.json                            │\\n   309→│     │   (checkpoint_id: \\\"a3b2c4d5e6f7\\\")          │\\n   310→│     ├── 0/                                       │\\n   311→│     │   ├── full.jsonl                           │\\n   312→│     │   ├── prompt.txt                           │\\n   313→│     │   └── context.md                           │\\n   314→│     └── ...                                      │\\n   315→│                                                   │\\n   316→│   Trailers:                                      │\\n   317→│     Entire-Session: 2026-01-20-uuid              │\\n   318→│     Entire-Strategy: manual-commit               │\\n   319→└──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\\n   320→```\\n   321→\\n   322→The checkpoint ID creates a **bidirectional link**: user commits can find their metadata, and metadata can find the commits that reference it.\\n   323→\\n   324→### Package Structure\\n   325→\\n   326→```\\n   327→strategy/\\n   328→├── session.go           # Session and Checkpoint types, ListSessions(), GetSession()\\n   329→\\n   330→session/\\n   331→├── state.go             # Active session state (StateStore, .git/entire-sessions/)\\n   332→├── phase.go             # Session phase state machine (ACTIVE, IDLE, ENDED, etc.)\\n   333→\\n   334→checkpoint/\\n   335→├── checkpoint.go        # checkpoint.Type, checkpoint.Store interface, CheckpointSummary, etc.\\n   336→├── store.go             # GitStore implementation\\n   337→├── temporary.go         # Shadow branch storage\\n   338→├── committed.go         # Metadata branch storage\\n   339→├── id/                  # CheckpointID type and generation\\n   340→│   └── id.go\\n   341→```\\n   342→\\n   343→Strategies use `checkpoint.Store` primitives - storage details are encapsulated.\\n   344→\\n   345→## Strategy Role\\n   346→\\n   347→Strategies determine checkpoint timing and type:\\n   348→\\n   349→| Strategy | On Save | On Task Complete | On User Commit |\\n   350→|----------|---------|------------------|----------------|\\n   351→| Manual-commit | Temporary | Temporary | Condense → Committed |\\n   352→| Auto-commit | Committed | Committed | — |\\n   353→\\n   354→## Rewind\\n   355→\\n   356→Each `RewindPoint` includes `SessionID` and `SessionPrompt` to help identify which checkpoint belongs to which session when multiple sessions are interleaved.\\n   357→\\n   358→## Concurrent Sessions\\n   359→\\n   360→Multiple AI sessions can run concurrently on the same base commit:\\n   361→\\n   362→1. **Warning on start** - When a second session starts while another has uncommitted checkpoints, a warning is shown\\n   363→2. **Both proceed** - User can continue; checkpoints interleave on the same shadow branch\\n   364→3. **Identification** - Each checkpoint is tagged with its session ID; rewind UI shows session prompt\\n   365→4. **Condensation** - On commit, all sessions are condensed together with archived subfolders\\n   366→\\n   367→### Conflict Handling\\n   368→\\n   369→| Scenario | Behavior |\\n   370→|----------|----------|\\n   371→| Concurrent sessions (same worktree) | Warning shown, both proceed |\\n   372→| Orphaned shadow branch (no state file) | Branch reset, new session proceeds |\\n   373→| Cross-worktree conflict (state file exists) | `SessionIDConflictError` returned |\\n   374→\\n   375→### Shadow Branch Migration\\n   376→\\n   377→If user does stash → pull → apply (HEAD changes without commit):\\n   378→- Detection: base commit changed AND old shadow branch still exists\\n   379→- Action: branch renamed from `entire/<old-commit[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>` to `entire/<new-commit[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>`\\n   380→- Result: session continues with checkpoints preserved\\n   381→\\n   382→---\\n   383→\\n   384→## Appendix: Legacy Names\\n   385→\\n   386→| Current | Legacy |\\n   387→|---------|--------|\\n   388→| Manual-commit | Shadow |\\n   389→| Auto-commit | Dual |\\n   390→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"7e405925-b3c5-4ee6-a0c0-b8b3e36cd6b3\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-25T04:04:42.879Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1/docs/architecture/sessions-and-checkpoints.md\",\"content\":\"# Sessions and Checkpoints\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nEntire CLI creates checkpoints for AI coding sessions. The system is agent-agnostic - it works with Claude Code, Gemini CLI, OpenCode, or any tool that triggers Entire hooks.\\n\\n## Domain Model\\n\\n### Session\\n\\nA **Session** is a unit of work. Defined in `strategy/session.go`:\\n\\n```go\\ntype Session struct {\\n    ID          string       // e.g., \\\"2025-12-01-8f76b0e8-b8f1-4a87-9186-848bdd83d62e\\\"\\n    Description string       // Human-readable summary (first prompt or derived)\\n    Strategy    string       // Strategy that created this session\\n    StartTime   time.Time\\n    Checkpoints []Checkpoint\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Checkpoint\\n\\nA **Checkpoint** captures a point-in-time within a session. Defined in `strategy/session.go`:\\n\\n```go\\ntype Checkpoint struct {\\n    CheckpointID     id.CheckpointID // Stable 12-hex-char identifier\\n    Message          string          // Commit message or checkpoint description\\n    Timestamp        time.Time\\n    IsTaskCheckpoint bool            // Task checkpoint (subagent) vs session checkpoint\\n    ToolUseID        string          // Tool use ID for task checkpoints (empty for session)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Checkpoint Types\\n\\nThe low-level `checkpoint.Type` (from `checkpoint/checkpoint.go`) indicates storage location:\\n\\n```go\\ntype Type int\\n\\nconst (\\n    Temporary Type = iota // Full state snapshot, shadow branch\\n    Committed             // Metadata + commit ref, entire/checkpoints/v1\\n)\\n```\\n\\n| Type | Contents | Use Case |\\n|------|----------|----------|\\n| Temporary | Full state (code + metadata) | Intra-session rewind, pre-commit |\\n| Committed | Metadata + commit reference | Permanent record, post-commit rewind |\\n\\n## Interface\\n\\n### Session Operations\\n\\nSessions are accessed via standalone functions in `strategy/session.go`:\\n\\n```go\\n// ListSessions returns all sessions from entire/checkpoints/v1,\\n// plus additional sessions from strategies implementing SessionSource.\\nfunc ListSessions() ([]Session, error)\\n\\n// GetSession finds a session by ID (supports prefix matching).\\nfunc GetSession(sessionID string) (*Session, error)\\n```\\n\\n### Checkpoint Storage (Low-Level)\\n\\nThe `checkpoint.Store` interface (from `checkpoint/checkpoint.go`) provides primitives for reading/writing checkpoints. Used by strategies.\\n\\n```go\\ntype Store interface {\\n    // Temporary checkpoint operations (shadow branches - full state)\\n    WriteTemporary(ctx context.Context, opts WriteTemporaryOptions) (WriteTemporaryResult, error)\\n    ReadTemporary(ctx context.Context, baseCommit, worktreeID string) (*ReadTemporaryResult, error)\\n    ListTemporary(ctx context.Context) ([]TemporaryInfo, error)\\n\\n    // Committed checkpoint operations (entire/checkpoints/v1 branch - metadata only)\\n    WriteCommitted(ctx context.Context, opts WriteCommittedOptions) error\\n    ReadCommitted(ctx context.Context, checkpointID id.CheckpointID) (*CheckpointSummary, error)\\n    ReadSessionContent(ctx context.Context, checkpointID id.CheckpointID, sessionIndex int) (*SessionContent, error)\\n    ReadSessionContentByID(ctx context.Context, checkpointID id.CheckpointID, sessionID string) (*SessionContent, error)\\n    ListCommitted(ctx context.Context) ([]CommittedInfo, error)\\n}\\n```\\n\\nKey option types (abbreviated):\\n\\n```go\\ntype WriteTemporaryOptions struct {\\n    SessionID      string\\n    BaseCommit     string\\n    WorktreeID     string   // Internal git worktree identifier (empty for main)\\n    ModifiedFiles  []string\\n    NewFiles       []string\\n    DeletedFiles   []string\\n    MetadataDir    string   // Relative path to metadata directory\\n    MetadataDirAbs string   // Absolute path\\n    CommitMessage  string\\n    // ...\\n}\\n\\ntype WriteCommittedOptions struct {\\n    CheckpointID id.CheckpointID\\n    SessionID    string\\n    Strategy     string\\n    Branch       string\\n    Transcript   []byte\\n    Prompts      []string\\n    Context      []byte\\n    FilesTouched []string\\n    TokenUsage   *agent.TokenUsage\\n    // ...\\n}\\n```\\n\\nToken usage is defined in `agent/types.go`:\\n\\n```go\\ntype TokenUsage struct {\\n    InputTokens         int         `json:\\\"input_tokens\\\"`\\n    CacheCreationTokens int         `json:\\\"cache_creation_tokens\\\"`\\n    CacheReadTokens     int         `json:\\\"cache_read_tokens\\\"`\\n    OutputTokens        int         `json:\\\"output_tokens\\\"`\\n    APICallCount        int         `json:\\\"api_call_count\\\"`\\n    SubagentTokens      *TokenUsage `json:\\\"subagent_tokens,omitempty\\\"`\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Strategy-Level Operations\\n\\nStrategies compose low-level primitives into higher-level workflows.\\n\\n**Manual-commit** has condensation logic:\\n\\n```go\\n// CondenseSession reads accumulated temporary state and writes a committed checkpoint.\\nfunc (s *ManualCommitStrategy) CondenseSession(\\n    repo *git.Repository,\\n    checkpointID id.CheckpointID,\\n    state *SessionState,\\n) (*CondenseResult, error)\\n```\\n\\n## Storage\\n\\n| Type | Location | Contents |\\n|------|----------|----------|\\n| Session State | `.git/entire-sessions/<id>.json` | Active session tracking |\\n| Temporary | `entire/<commit[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>` branch | Full state (code + metadata) |\\n| Committed | `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch (sharded) | Metadata + commit reference |\\n\\n### Session State\\n\\nLocation: `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json`\\n\\nStored in git common dir (shared across worktrees). Tracks active session info.\\n\\n### Temporary Checkpoints\\n\\nBranch: `entire/<commit[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>`\\n\\nContains full worktree snapshot plus metadata overlay. **Multiple concurrent sessions** can share the same shadow branch - their checkpoints interleave:\\n\\n```\\n<worktree files...>\\n.entire/metadata/<session-id-1>/\\n├── full.jsonl           # Session 1 transcript\\n├── prompt.txt           # User prompts\\n├── context.md           # Generated context\\n└── tasks/<tool-use-id>/ # Task checkpoints\\n.entire/metadata/<session-id-2>/\\n├── full.jsonl           # Session 2 transcript (concurrent)\\n├── ...\\n```\\n\\nTied to a base commit. Condensed to committed on user commit.\\n\\n**Shadow branch lifecycle:**\\n- Created on first checkpoint for a base commit\\n- Migrated automatically if base commit changes (stash → pull → apply scenario)\\n- Deleted after condensation to `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n- Reset if orphaned (no session state file exists)\\n\\n### Committed Checkpoints\\n\\nBranch: `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n\\nMetadata only, sharded by checkpoint ID. Supports **multiple sessions per checkpoint**:\\n\\n```\\n<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/\\n├── metadata.json        # CheckpointSummary (aggregated stats)\\n├── 0/                   # First session (0-based indexing)\\n│   ├── metadata.json    # Session-specific CommittedMetadata\\n│   ├── full.jsonl\\n│   ├── prompt.txt\\n│   ├── context.md\\n│   └── content_hash.txt\\n├── 1/                   # Second session\\n│   ├── metadata.json\\n│   ├── full.jsonl\\n│   └── ...\\n└── 2/                   # Third session...\\n```\\n\\n**Root-level metadata.json (`CheckpointSummary`):**\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"checkpoint_id\\\": \\\"abc123def456\\\",\\n  \\\"strategy\\\": \\\"manual-commit\\\",\\n  \\\"branch\\\": \\\"main\\\",\\n  \\\"checkpoints_count\\\": 3,\\n  \\\"files_touched\\\": [\\\"file1.txt\\\", \\\"file2.txt\\\"],\\n  \\\"sessions\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"metadata\\\": \\\"/ab/c123def456/0/metadata.json\\\",\\n      \\\"transcript\\\": \\\"/ab/c123def456/0/full.jsonl\\\",\\n      \\\"context\\\": \\\"/ab/c123def456/0/context.md\\\",\\n      \\\"content_hash\\\": \\\"/ab/c123def456/0/content_hash.txt\\\",\\n      \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"/ab/c123def456/0/prompt.txt\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"token_usage\\\": {\\n    \\\"input_tokens\\\": 1500,\\n    \\\"cache_creation_tokens\\\": 200,\\n    \\\"cache_read_tokens\\\": 800,\\n    \\\"output_tokens\\\": 500,\\n    \\\"api_call_count\\\": 3\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nWhen condensing multiple concurrent sessions:\\n- All sessions are stored in numbered subdirectories using 0-based indexing (`0/`, `1/`, `2/`, ...)\\n- Each `session_id` is assigned a stable index; subsequent writes for the same session reuse the same numbered folder\\n- New `session_id` values are appended at the next index, so higher-numbered folders correspond to more recently introduced sessions, not necessarily the chronologically latest activity\\n- `sessions` array in `CheckpointSummary` maps each session to its file paths\\n- `files_touched` is merged from all sessions\\n\\n### Checkpoint ID Linking\\n\\nThe checkpoint ID is the **stable identifier** that links user commits to metadata across branches.\\n\\n**Format:** 12-hex-character random ID (e.g., `a3b2c4d5e6f7`)\\n\\n**Generation:**\\n- Manual-commit: Generated during condensation (post-commit hook)\\n- Auto-commit: Generated when creating the commit\\n\\n**Usage:**\\n\\n1. **User commit trailer** (both strategies):\\n   - `Entire-Checkpoint: a3b2c4d5e6f7` added to user's commit message\\n   - Auto-commit: Added programmatically\\n   - Manual-commit: Added by `prepare-commit-msg` hook (user can remove)\\n\\n2. **Directory sharding** on `entire/checkpoints/v1`:\\n   - Path: `<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/` (e.g., `a3/b2c4d5e6f7/`)\\n   - First 2 chars = shard (256 possible shards)\\n   - Remaining 10 chars = directory name\\n\\n3. **Commit subject** on `entire/checkpoints/v1`:\\n   - Format: `Checkpoint: a3b2c4d5e6f7`\\n   - Makes `git log entire/checkpoints/v1` readable\\n\\n**Bidirectional Lookup:**\\n\\n```\\nUser commit → Metadata:\\n  1. Extract \\\"Entire-Checkpoint: a3b2c4d5e6f7\\\" from commit message\\n  2. Read entire/checkpoints/v1 tree at a3/b2c4d5e6f7/\\n\\nMetadata → User commits:\\n  Given checkpoint ID a3b2c4d5e6f7\\n  → Search branch history for commits with \\\"Entire-Checkpoint: a3b2c4d5e6f7\\\"\\n```\\n\\nNote: Commit subjects on `entire/checkpoints/v1` (e.g., `Checkpoint: a3b2c4d5e6f7`)\\nare for human readability in `git log` only. The CLI always reads from the tree at HEAD.\\n\\n**Example Flow:**\\n\\n```\\n                    User creates commit\\n                           ↓\\n           prepare-commit-msg hook adds trailer\\n                           ↓\\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\\n│ Commit on main branch:                           │\\n│   \\\"Implement login feature                       │\\n│                                                   │\\n│   Entire-Checkpoint: a3b2c4d5e6f7\\\"               │\\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\\n                           ↓\\n                  post-commit hook runs\\n                           ↓\\n          Condense shadow → entire/checkpoints/v1\\n                           ↓\\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\\n│ Commit on entire/checkpoints/v1:                 │\\n│   Subject: \\\"Checkpoint: a3b2c4d5e6f7\\\"            │\\n│                                                   │\\n│   Tree: a3/b2c4d5e6f7/                           │\\n│     ├── metadata.json                            │\\n│     │   (checkpoint_id: \\\"a3b2c4d5e6f7\\\")          │\\n│     ├── 0/                                       │\\n│     │   ├── full.jsonl                           │\\n│     │   ├── prompt.txt                           │\\n│     │   └── context.md                           │\\n│     └── ...                                      │\\n│                                                   │\\n│   Trailers:                                      │\\n│     Entire-Session: 2026-01-20-uuid              │\\n│     Entire-Strategy: manual-commit               │\\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\\n```\\n\\nThe checkpoint ID creates a **bidirectional link**: user commits can find their metadata, and metadata can find the commits that reference it.\\n\\n### Package Structure\\n\\n```\\nstrategy/\\n├── session.go           # Session and Checkpoint types, ListSessions(), GetSession()\\n\\nsession/\\n├── state.go             # Active session state (StateStore, .git/entire-sessions/)\\n├── phase.go             # Session phase state machine (ACTIVE, IDLE, ENDED, etc.)\\n\\ncheckpoint/\\n├── checkpoint.go        # checkpoint.Type, checkpoint.Store interface, CheckpointSummary, etc.\\n├── store.go             # GitStore implementation\\n├── temporary.go         # Shadow branch storage\\n├── committed.go         # Metadata branch storage\\n├── id/                  # CheckpointID type and generation\\n│   └── id.go\\n```\\n\\nStrategies use `checkpoint.Store` primitives - storage details are encapsulated.\\n\\n## Strategy Role\\n\\nStrategies determine checkpoint timing and type:\\n\\n| Strategy | On Save | On Task Complete | On User Commit |\\n|----------|---------|------------------|----------------|\\n| Manual-commit | Temporary | Temporary | Condense → Committed |\\n| Auto-commit | Committed | Committed | — |\\n\\n## Rewind\\n\\nEach `RewindPoint` includes `SessionID` and `SessionPrompt` to help identify which checkpoint belongs to which session when multiple sessions are interleaved.\\n\\n## Concurrent Sessions\\n\\nMultiple AI sessions can run concurrently on the same base commit:\\n\\n1. **Warning on start** - When a second session starts while another has uncommitted checkpoints, a warning is shown\\n2. **Both proceed** - User can continue; checkpoints interleave on the same shadow branch\\n3. **Identification** - Each checkpoint is tagged with its session ID; rewind UI shows session prompt\\n4. **Condensation** - On commit, all sessions are condensed together with archived subfolders\\n\\n### Conflict Handling\\n\\n| Scenario | Behavior |\\n|----------|----------|\\n| Concurrent sessions (same worktree) | Warning shown, both proceed |\\n| Orphaned shadow branch (no state file) | Branch reset, new session proceeds |\\n| Cross-worktree conflict (state file exists) | `SessionIDConflictError` returned |\\n\\n### Shadow Branch Migration\\n\\nIf user does stash → pull → apply (HEAD changes without commit):\\n- Detection: base commit changed AND old shadow branch still exists\\n- Action: branch renamed from `entire/<old-commit[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>` to `entire/<new-commit[:7]>-<worktreeHash[:6]>`\\n- Result: session continues with checkpoints preserved\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Appendix: Legacy Names\\n\\n| Current | Legacy |\\n|---------|--------|\\n| Manual-commit | Shadow |\\n| Auto-commit | Dual |\\n\",\"numLines\":390,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":390}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"131cf96d-b659-4345-b332-8f33edf77683\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"7e405925-b3c5-4ee6-a0c0-b8b3e36cd6b3\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"61641d7f-fa2a-419c-9e05-a950f1647e51\",\"version\":\"2.1.53\",\"gitBranch\":\"remove-auto-commit\",\"slug\":\"crispy-gathering-origami\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_015oJGy86WTMHu3xaeuH6yw9\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01RcUCjCiqXASZSPpWWDUq6P\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1/.claude/agents/reviewer.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":4227,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":106469,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":4227},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYU8C94yxu3ZbPfgdxx3S\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"0618c142-0a00-412f-a6e7-a04ef22e6af8\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-25T04:04:43.266Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"0618c142-0a00-412f-a6e7-a04ef22e6af8\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"61641d7f-fa2a-419c-9e05-a950f1647e51\",\"version\":\"2.1.53\",\"